Title: A Toy for the Infanta
Description: In 1833, the death of the King creates a struggle for the throne of Spain. The Count of Monte Cristo supports the claim of the King's widow who seeks to reign as regent for her young daughter, the Infanta.
Short Description: In 1833, the death of the King creates a struggle for the throne of Spain.

Title: Marseilles
Description: The Count goes undercover on the Marseilles waterfront to expose a piracy ring preying on ships bound from Spain.
Short Description: The Count goes undercover on the Marseilles waterfront to expose a piracy ring.

Title: The Luxembourg Affair
Description: A scheming General replaces the Grand Duchess of Luxembourg with an impostor in the year 1836. The Count, summoned on financial matters, sees through the impostor and works to bring back the true Grand Duchess.
Short Description: A scheming General replaces the Grand Duchess of Luxembourg with an impostor in the year 1836.

Title: The Texas Affair
Description: An emissary from Texas arrives in France, seeking recognition for his new country. He's attacked by men paid by the Mexican government, but is then defended by the Count of Monte Cristo.
Short Description: An emissary from Texas arrives in France, seeking recognition for his new country.

Title: The Mazzini Affair
Description: The Count, disguised as a priest, enters a fortress where a rebel -- seeking to free Italy from Austria's yoke -- faces execution.
Short Description: The Count, disguised as a priest, enters a fortress where a rebel -- seeking to free Italy from Austria's yoke -- faces execution.

Title: The Carbonari
Description: The Count intervenes on behalf of a man who's being blackmailed by a secret society known as the Carbonari.
Short Description: The Count intervenes on behalf of a man who's being blackmailed by a secret society known as the Carbonari.

Title: The Devil's Emissary
Description: Residents of an Alpine valley are being held prisoner by a man rumored to be dabbling in the black arts. The Count of Monte Cristo arrives to investigate.
Short Description: Residents of an Alpine valley are being held prisoner by a man rumored to be dabbling in the black arts.

Title: Bordeaux
Description: Mercedes, the great love of the Count's early life, accepts the Count's help after her husband has been imprisoned and sentenced to death for a crime he did not commit.
Short Description: Mercedes, the great love of the Count's early life, accepts the Count's help after her husband has been imprisoned.

Title: Flight to Carais
Description: While traveling to England to be married, Princess Anne of France is kidnapped just outside Calais. The Count of Monte Cristo takes action to rescue her.
Short Description: While traveling to England to be married, Princess Anne of France is kidnapped just outside Calais.

Title: Albania
Description: A man claiming to be the Count of Monte Cristo has headquartered in Albania and is working with another man who wishes to become dictator of that country. The true Count travels to Tirana to set things right.
Short Description: A man claiming to be the Count of Monte Cristo has headquartered in Albania.

Title: The Coast of Italy
Description: The reading of a wealthy banker's will in Naples, Italy, produces unexpected results. The Count investigates and finds danger and deceit.
Short Description: The reading of a wealthy banker's will in Naples, Italy, produces unexpected results.

Title: The Act of Terror
Description: Masked men have taken over the waterfront in Le Havre, France, kidnapping and imprisoning sailors. No ship can sail without paying tribute to the leader of these men.
Short Description: Masked men have taken over the waterfront in Le Havre, France, kidnapping and imprisoning sailors.

Title: The Experiment
Description: A chemist is falsely accused of treason because of a discovery he's made in his lab. It seems another man covets the money to be made from this discovery.
Short Description: A chemist is falsely accused of treason because of a discovery he's made in his lab.

Title: Mecklenburg
Description: The heir to the French throne runs into trouble when he pays a secret visit to Mecklenburg. He wants to see there the princess he loves but she's been promised to another suitor and the French heir winds up in prison.
Short Description: The heir to the French throne runs into trouble when he pays a secret visit to Mecklenburg.

Title: The Portuguese Affair
Description: The Count travels to Portugal for a wedding but the groom is arrested just before the ceremony on murder charges. The Count investigates and finds a plot to overthrow the Portuguese government.
Short Description: The Count travels to Portugal for a wedding but the groom is arrested just before the ceremony on murder charges.

Title: Lichtenburg
Description: The death of the King of Lichtenburg creates a power struggle. Princess Anne, the rightful heir, finds herself imprisoned in the palace by an ambitious man anxious to assume power. The Count seeks to help her.
Short Description: The death of the King of Lichtenburg creates a power struggle.

Title: Burgundy
Description: A grape-grower in Burgundy seeks help after he's forced to pay tribute to a man claiming to be able to bring about a tax cut. The Count investigates and uncovers a fraud.
Short Description: A grape-grower in Burgundy seeks help after he's forced to pay tribute to a man claiming to be able to bring about a tax cut.

Title: Majorca
Description: Edmond Dantes, who escaped the prison at Chateau d’if uses the treasure the Abbe told him of to extend justice to those in need.
Short Description: Edmond Dantes, who escaped the prison at Chateau d’if uses the treasure the Abbe told him of to extend justice to those in need.

Title: Sicily
Description: Years ago in Sicily, the young Edmund -- before he became the Count of Monte Cristo -- confronts a corrupt banker and restores to its rightful owner a farm stolen by that banker.
Short Description: Years ago in Sicily, the young Edmund -- before he became the Count of Monte Cristo -- confronts a corrupt banker

Title: A Matter of Justice
Description: A mother's plea that her soldier-son has been unjustly sentenced to Devil's Island prompts the Count to investigate. He discovers a web of corruption involving two officers in the French army.
Short Description: A mother's plea that her soldier-son has been unjustly sentenced to Devil's Island prompts the Count to investigate.

Title: Athens
Description: The murder in Athens of a dealer in Greek antiquities leads the Count to the recovery of an ancient statue being smuggled out of the country.
Short Description: The murder in Athens of a dealer in Greek antiquities leads the Count to the recovery of an ancient statue being smuggled out of the country.

Title: The Tallyrand Affair
Description: Desperate to thwart a plan to form the country of Belgium out of Netherlands territory, the Duchess of Maastricht kidnaps the son of one of the plan's proponents. The Count seeks to rescue the son, and the plan.
Short Description: The Duchess of Maastricht kidnaps the son of one of the plan's proponents.

Title: The Island
Description: Rico is drugged, kidnapped, and whipped to make him reveal the location of the Count's treasure. The Count mounts a rescue, which involves a Duchess who schemes to put a Bonaparte back into power in Paris.
Short Description: Rico is drugged, kidnapped, and whipped to make him reveal the location of the Count's treasure.

Title: The Barefoot Empress
Description: En route to Versailles, the young Empress of Austria is beset by a party of assassins. The Count seeks to save her despite her sometimes lack of cooperation.
Short Description: En route to Versailles, the young Empress of Austria is beset by a party of assassins.

Title: The Grecian Gift
Description: Twin sons of a inventor clash over control of what might be their father's greatest achievement -- a screw-propeller attached to a ship's steam engine. Such an invention would revolutionize naval warfare and maritime shipping.
Short Description: Twin sons of a inventor clash over control of what might be their father's greatest achievement -- a screw-propeller attached to a ship's steam engine.

Title: Monaco
Description: A printer tries to live down his counterfeiting past but his young, greedy wife has other ideas. She becomes involved in illegal dealings at the Monte Carlo casino and it takes the Count of Monte Cristo to sort things out.
Short Description: A printer tries to live down his counterfeiting past but his young, greedy wife has other ideas.

Title: Point Counterpoint
Description: A woman, falsely believing the Count murdered her father, frames him on a smuggling charge by substituting arms inside cases bound for the Count's new chateau.
Short Description: A woman, falsely believing the Count murdered her father, frames him on a smuggling charge.

Title: The Black Death
Description: A doctor tries to stem the spread of a plague in Paris but is thwarted by forces of greed and ignorance. The Count lends his support to the doctor and many lives are then saved.
Short Description: A doctor tries to stem the spread of a plague in Paris but is thwarted by forces of greed and ignorance.

Title: Victor Hugo
Description: Surprised to learn of Victor Hugo's unwavering faith in the French judicial system, the Count uses a turn of events to change Hugo's mind. Hugo then determines to write a book about the system called "Les Miserables."
Short Description: Surprised to learn of Victor Hugo's unwavering faith in the French judicial system, the Count uses a turn of events to change Hugo's mind.

Title: Return to the Chateau d'if
Description: In the Château d'If, the Count tells the story of his imprisonment.
Short Description: In the Château d'If, the Count tells the story of his imprisonment.

Title: The Pen and the Sword
Description: The Count seeks to uncover the theft of three million francs by someone known only as Veritas.
Short Description: The Count seeks to uncover the theft of three million francs by someone known only as Veritas.

Title: The Sardinian Affair
Description: Dantès's closest friend has been murdered, and Dantès challenges the murderer to a duel.
Short Description: Dantès's closest friend has been murdered, and Dantès challenges the murderer to a duel.

Title: The Affair of the Three Napoleons
Description: A young woman arrives at Dantes's mansion looking for help finding her father's murderer; the only clues are three gold coins she found clutched in his hands.
Short Description: A young woman arrives at Dantes's mansion looking for help finding her father's murderer.

Title: The Dubarry Affair
Description: Edmond Dantes, who escaped the prison at Chateau d’if uses the treasure the Abbe told him of to extend justice to those in need.
Short Description: Edmond Dantes, who escaped the prison at Chateau d’if uses the treasure the Abbe told him of to extend justice to those in need.

Title: The First Train to Paris
Description: The first steam train to Paris is destroyed in an explosion. A newspaper had reported this before it happened.
Short Description: The first steam train to Paris is destroyed in an explosion.

Title: The Golden Blade
Description: Edmond Dantes, who escaped the prison at Chateau d’if uses the treasure the Abbe told him of to extend justice to those in need.
Short Description: Edmond Dantes, who escaped the prison at Chateau d’if uses the treasure the Abbe told him of to extend justice to those in need.

Title: The Duel
Description: Edmond Dantes, who escaped the prison at Chateau d’if uses the treasure the Abbe told him of to extend justice to those in need.
Short Description: Edmond Dantes, who escaped the prison at Chateau d’if uses the treasure the Abbe told him of to extend justice to those in need.

Title: Andorra
Description: Dantes must protect a murdered duke's children from their maniacal uncle.
Short Description: Dantes must protect a murdered duke's children from their maniacal uncle.

Title: An Affair of Honour
Description: A young man is framed for the poisoning of his rival.
Short Description: A young man is framed for the poisoning of his rival.
